WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:02.800
sg_apicore helps developers define TYPO3

2
00:00:02.820 --> 00:00:05.755
web API endpoints in one

3
00:00:05.775 --> 00:00:07.770
place. They describe the address,

4
00:00:07.790 --> 00:00:10.230
access rules, and expected data

5
00:00:10.250 --> 00:00:12.410
beside the controller code.

6
00:00:12.430 --> 00:00:14.690
The extension then builds versioned

7
00:00:14.710 --> 00:00:17.275
routes and API documentation.

8
00:00:17.295 --> 00:00:18.960
It can also provide standard

9
00:00:18.980 --> 00:00:20.750
read-and-write operations for selected TYPO3

10
00:00:20.770 --> 00:00:24.005
tables and expose chosen endpoints

11
00:00:24.025 --> 00:00:25.735
to MCP clients.

12
00:00:25.755 --> 00:00:28.295
This reduces duplicate code.

13
00:00:28.315 --> 00:00:30.105
The feature page explains access

14
00:00:30.125 --> 00:00:31.400
and data handling.
